# Frontend environment template (gsheets-backend branch — DIRECT mode).
# Copy to `.env`.

# The ONLY var this branch needs. Google OAuth Client ID (Web application) —
# the same one used for the Calendar export. When set, lib/gsApi.js flips
# isConfigured=true and the app stores everything DIRECTLY in Google
# Drive/Sheets (no server): a "Productivity-Shastra-Data" root folder is
# auto-created in the Drive of whoever completes the consent popup, with a
# _System spreadsheet (users registry) and one folder per signed-up user
# containing the five tool spreadsheets.
# Requires "Google Sheets API" + "Google Drive API" enabled in the same
# Google Cloud project. When empty, the app runs in offline/localStorage
# demo mode.
VITE_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=
